{
  "text": "The cutoff values for serum testosterone levels in diagnosing hypogonadism differ among institutions and research groups. For example, the International Society for the Study of the Aging Male (ISSAM) regards a serum tT level of <3.17 ng/mL as indicating hypogonadism [CITATION_1] . In the present study, we regarded a serum tT level of \u22642.7 ng/mL or a serum free testosterone (fT) level of \u226410 pg/mL as indicating hypogonadism.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "28291459"
  },
